<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_rnf_3cb_qy">
    <title>Uninstalling the Tarball (Service Start)</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>uninstallation<indexterm>tarball service
                    start</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>tarball service
                        start<indexterm>uninstallation</indexterm></indexterm>To uninstall a <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> instance that was installed from the tarball and started as a service, shut down
                    <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> and then remove all <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> directories.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Use one of the following methods to shut down <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    />:</cmd>
                <choices id="choices_hwp_k2c_rx">
                    <choice>To use the command line, use the required command for your operating
                            system.<p
                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/shutdownServiceLinuxEL6"
                            conrefend="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/shutdownServiceLinuxEL7"
                        /></choice>
                    <choice>
                        <p
                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/shutdownUI"
                        />
                    </choice>
                </choices>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Remove the <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    /> directories.</cmd>
                <info>For example, if you used the default directories on Red Hat Enterprise Linux
                    6, run the following command to remove the directories:
                    <codeblock>rm -rf /etc/init.d/sdc  /etc/sdc /var/log/sdc /var/lib/sdc /var/lib/sdc-resources</codeblock></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Remove the directory where you extracted the tarball.</cmd>
                <info>For example, if you extracted the tarball to <codeph>/opt/local/</codeph>, run
                    the following command to remove the
                    directory:<codeblock>rm -rf /opt/local/</codeblock></info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
    <related-links>
        <link href="../Configuration/DCDirectories.dita#concept_mnx_j3r_3v"/>
    </related-links>
</task>
